attributeList.name: abbreviation
attributeList.doc: Common abbreviation used to refer to amino acids.

attributeList.name: cid
attributeList.doc: PubChem Compound ID (CID) for the molecule.

attributeList.name: spin
attributeList.doc: Total spin number of the molecule.

attributeList.name: basis
attributeList.doc: Basis set used for the quantum chemistry calculations.

attributeList.name: bond_length
attributeList.doc: Specific bond length set from the coordinates in Angstroms.

attributeList.name: symbols
attributeList.doc: List of atomic symbols (e.g., H, C, N, O) corresponding to each atom.

attributeList.name: coordinates
attributeList.doc: List of 3D Cartesian coordinates (x, y, z) for each atom.

attributeList.name: n_atoms
attributeList.doc: Total number of atoms in the molecule.

attributeList.name: n_electrons
attributeList.doc: Number of electrons present in the system.

attributeList.name: n_orbitals
attributeList.doc: Number of molecular orbitals used in the simulation.

attributeList.name: n_qubits
attributeList.doc: Number of qubits required to simulate the system in quantum computations.

attributeList.name: n_coefficients
attributeList.doc: Number of coefficients in the Hamiltonian or wavefunction representation.

attributeList.name: hamiltonian_n
attributeList.doc: Fragment of the total Hamiltonian in the Pauli basis. Each `hamiltonian_n` corresponds to a part of the full operator, which must be concatenated in numerical order (e.g., `hamiltonian`, `hamiltonian_1`, `hamiltonian_2`, ...) to reconstruct the complete Hamiltonian. This splitting is used due to the length of the full expression.

attributeList.name: energy
attributeList.doc: Ground state energy of the system in Hartrees, computed using the Self-Consistent Field (SCF) approach based on the Hartree-Fock method.
